  "chapter": {
    "number": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Mountain of the House of the LORD"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is the message that was revealed to Isaiah son of Amoz concerning Judah and Jerusalem:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the last days the mountain of the house of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be established as the chief of the mountains;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "it will be raised above the hills,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all nations will stream to it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And many peoples will come and say:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Come, let us go up to the mountain of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the house of the God of Jacob.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will teach us His ways",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that we may walk in His paths.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "For the law will go forth from Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the word of the LORD from Jerusalem.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then He will judge between the nations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and arbitrate for many peoples.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will beat their swords into plowshares",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their spears into pruning hooks.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Nation will no longer take up the sword against nation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor train anymore for war.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Day of Reckoning"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Come, O house of Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let us walk in the light of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For You have abandoned Your people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the house of Jacob,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because they are filled",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with influences from the east;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they are soothsayers like the Philistines;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they strike hands with the children of foreigners.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their land is full of silver and gold,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with no limit to their treasures;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their land is full of horses,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with no limit to their chariots.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their land is full of idols;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they bow down to the work of their hands,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to what their fingers have made.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So mankind is brought low,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and man is humbled—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "do not forgive them!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Go into the rocks",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and hide in the dust",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "from the terror of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the splendor of His majesty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The proud look of man will be humbled,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the loftiness of men brought low;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD alone will be exalted in that day.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the Day of the LORD of Hosts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will come against all the proud and lofty,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "against all that is exalted—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will be humbled—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "against all the cedars of Lebanon, lofty and lifted up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against all the oaks of Bashan,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "against all the tall mountains,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against all the high hills,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "against every high tower,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against every fortified wall,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "against every ship of Tarshish,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2514
          },
          {
            "text": "and against every stately vessel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So the pride of man will be brought low,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the loftiness of men will be humbled;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD alone will be exalted in that day,",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "and the idols will vanish completely.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Men will flee to caves in the rocks",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and holes in the ground,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "away from the terror of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and from the splendor of His majesty,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when He rises to shake the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In that day men will cast away",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the moles and bats",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their idols of silver and gold—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the idols they made to worship.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will flee to caverns in the rocks",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and crevices in the cliffs,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "away from the terror of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and from the splendor of His majesty,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when He rises to shake the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put no more trust in man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who has only the breath in his nostrils.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Of what account is he?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2514,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or every ship of trade",
